DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T230000
SUMMARY:Chester County Pastoral Hike
DESCRIPTION:Metrotrails: NJ\, PA\, NY Metropolitan Area Hiking and More!\n
 Join us for this excellent rural hike in Chester County PA\, which ties to
 gether a different way the recent Chester County hikes we've been doing.\n
 From the start\, we will do the easier back roads.\nThe only lined road we
  will be on is the very beginning.\nWe will walk through the historic Shee
 der-Hall Covered Bridge\, then out to the main road for under a half mile\
 , We then turn onto some back roads including Sheeder Mill Road\, HIlltop 
 Road\, Birchrun Road\, Green Lane\, and Bartlett Road.\nAt least half of t
 his is unpaved\, and none of these named roads even have lines in them\, m
 aking them narrow\, lightly used\, and very pleasant.\nWe'll soon get on t
 he Horse-Shoe Trail from where we left off. This takes us through pleasant
  woods\, and then out into cultivated farm fields.\nBits of the Horse-Shoe
  Trail also follow these little used roads.\nWe'll continue on the HST to 
 Art School Lane\, then make our way east and pass the historic Vincent Bap
 tist Church and cemetery.\nWe'll continue to the intersection with Miller 
 Road\, where we'll begin following the Bryn Coed Trail System.\nThis amazi
 ng and long trail system weaves though woods and fields keeping with the o
 verall theme of the hike.\nAmazing pastoral views will make for a relaxing
  walk that will lead us almost all the way back to our stating point.\nWe'
 ll get on one more dirt road before the end\, and then an abandoned road t
 hat is now in the trail system right back to where we parked.\nIf needed\,
  contact me at 908 343 8374
